  <Name>k__BackingField: Colossians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: col
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: Paul, an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God, and Timothy our
        brother,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Their Faith in Christ'
      title: Their Faith in Christ
      number: 2
      content: To the saints and faithful brethren in Christ who  are in Colosse:Grace
        to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'We give thanks to the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, praying
        always for you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'since we heard of your faith in Christ Jesus and of your love for
        all the saints; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'because of the hope which is laid up for you in heaven, of which
        you heard before in the word of the truth of the gospel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'which has come to you, as it  has also in all the world, and is bringing
        forth fruit, as it  is also among you since the day you heard and knew the
        grace of God in truth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'as you also learned from Epaphras, our dear fellow servant, who is
        a faithful minister of Christ on your behalf, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Preeminence of Christ'
      title: Preeminence of Christ
      number: 8
      content: who also declared to us your love in the Spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For this reason we also, since the day we heard it, do not cease
        to pray for you, and to ask that you may be filled with the knowledge of
        His will in all wisdom and spiritual understanding; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'that you may walk worthy of the Lord, fully pleasing Him,  being
        fruitful in every good work and increasing in the knowledge of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'strengthened with all might, according to His glorious power, for
        all patience and longsuffering with joy; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'giving thanks to the Father who has qualified us to be partakers
        of the inheritance of the saints in the light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He has delivered us from the power of darkness and conveyed us into
        the kingdom of the Son of His love, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: in whom we have redemption through His blood, the forgiveness of sins.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn over all creation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For by Him all things were created that are in heaven and that are
        on earth, visible and invisible, whether thrones or dominions or principalities
        or powers. All things were created through Him and for Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And He is before all things, and in Him all things consist. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Reconciled in Christ'
      title: Reconciled in Christ
      number: 18
      content: And He is the head of the body, the church, who is the beginning,
        the firstborn from the dead, that in all things He may have the preeminence.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For it pleased the  Father  that  in Him all the fullness should
        dwell, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: and by Him to reconcile all things to Himself, by Him, whether things
        on earth or things in heaven, having made peace through the blood of His
        cross.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And you, who once were alienated and enemies in your mind by wicked
        works, yet now He has reconciled '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "in the body of His flesh through death, to present you holy, and
        blameless, and above reproach in His sight\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Sacrificial Service for Christ'
      title: Sacrificial Service for Christ
      number: 23
      content: if indeed you continue in the faith, grounded and steadfast, and are
        not moved away from the hope of the gospel which you heard, which was preached
        to every creature under heaven, of which I, Paul, became a minister.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'I now rejoice in my sufferings for you, and fill up in my flesh what
        is lacking in the afflictions of Christ, for the sake of His body, which
        is the church, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'of which I became a minister according to the stewardship from God
        which was given to me for you, to fulfill the word of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'the mystery which has been hidden from ages and from generations,
        but now has been revealed to His saints. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'To them God willed to make known what are the riches of the glory
        of this mystery among the Gentiles: which is Christ in you, the hope of glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Him we preach, warning every man and teaching every man in all wisdom,
        that we may present every man perfect in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: To this end I also labor, striving according to His working which
        works in me mightily.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Not Philosophy but Christ'
      title: Not Philosophy but Christ
      number: 1
      content: 'For I want you to know what a great conflict I have for you and those
        in Laodicea, and for as many as have not seen my face in the flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that their hearts may be encouraged, being knit together in love,
        and attaining to all riches of the full assurance of understanding, to the
        knowledge of the mystery of God, both of the Father and of Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: in whom are hidden all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now this I say lest anyone should deceive you with persuasive words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: For though I am absent in the flesh, yet I am with you in spirit,
        rejoicing to see your good order and the steadfastness of your faith in Christ.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As you therefore have received Christ Jesus the Lord, so walk in
        Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: rooted and built up in Him and established in the faith, as you have
        been taught, abounding in it with thanksgiving.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Beware lest anyone cheat you through philosophy and empty deceit,
        according to the tradition of men, according to the basic principles of the
        world, and not according to Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For in Him dwells all the fullness of the Godhead bodily; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Not Legalism but Christ'
      title: Not Legalism but Christ
      number: 10
      content: and you are complete in Him, who is the head of all principality and
        power.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In Him you were also circumcised with the circumcision made without
        hands, by putting off the body of the sins of the flesh, by the circumcision
        of Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'buried with Him in baptism, in which you also were raised with Him
        through faith in the working of God, who raised Him from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And you, being dead in your trespasses and the uncircumcision of
        your flesh, He has made alive together with Him, having forgiven you all
        trespasses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'having wiped out the handwriting of requirements that was against
        us, which was contrary to us. And He has taken it out of the way, having
        nailed it to the cross. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Having disarmed principalities and powers, He made a public spectacle
        of them, triumphing over them in it.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So let no one judge you in food or in drink, or regarding a festival
        or a new moon or sabbaths, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'which are a shadow of things to come, but the substance is of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let no one cheat you of your reward, taking delight in false humility
        and worship of angels, intruding into those things which he has not seen,
        vainly puffed up by his fleshly mind, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: and not holding fast to the Head, from whom all the body, nourished
        and knit together by joints and ligaments, grows with the increase that 
        is from God.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Therefore, if you died with Christ from the basic principles of the
        world, why, as though living in the world, do you subject yourselves to regulations\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CDo not touch, do not taste, do not handle,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "which all concern things which perish with the using\u2014according
        to the commandments and doctrines of men? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: These things indeed have an appearance of wisdom in self-imposed religion,
        false humility, and neglect of the body, but  are of no value against the
        indulgence of the flesh.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Not Carnality but Christ'
      title: Not Carnality but Christ
      number: 1
      content: 'If then you were raised with Christ, seek those things which are
        above, where Christ is, sitting at the right hand of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Set your mind on things above, not on things on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For you died, and your life is hidden with Christ in God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: When Christ who  is  our life appears, then you also will appear with
        Him in glory.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore put to death your members which are on the earth: fornication,
        uncleanness, passion, evil desire, and covetousness, which is idolatry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Because of these things the wrath of God is coming upon the sons
        of disobedience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: in which you yourselves once walked when you lived in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But now you yourselves are to put off all these: anger, wrath, malice,
        blasphemy, filthy language out of your mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not lie to one another, since you have put off the old man with
        his deeds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and have put on the new man who is renewed in knowledge according
        to the image of Him who created him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Character of the New Man'
      title: Character of the New Man
      number: 11
      content: where there is neither Greek nor Jew, circumcised nor uncircumcised,
        barbarian, Scythian, slave nor free, but Christ is all and in all.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore, as the elect of God, holy and beloved, put on tender mercies,
        kindness, humility, meekness, longsuffering; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'bearing with one another, and forgiving one another, if anyone has
        a complaint against another; even as Christ forgave you, so you also must 
        do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But above all these things put on love, which is the bond of perfection. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to which also you were
        called in one body; and be thankful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Let the word of Christ dwell in you richly in all wisdom, teaching
        and admonishing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing
        with grace in your hearts to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Christian Home'
      title: The Christian Home
      number: 17
      content: And whatever you do in word or deed, do all in the name of the Lord
        Jesus, giving thanks to God the Father through Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Wives, submit to your own husbands, as is fitting in the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Husbands, love your wives and do not be bitter toward them.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Children, obey your parents in all things, for this is well pleasing
        to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Fathers, do not provoke your children, lest they become discouraged.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Bondservants, obey in all things your masters according to the flesh,
        not with eyeservice, as men-pleasers, but in sincerity of heart, fearing
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And whatever you do, do it heartily, as to the Lord and not to men, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'knowing that from the Lord you will receive the reward of the inheritance;
        for you serve the Lord Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But he who does wrong will be repaid for what he has done, and there
        is no partiality.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Christian Graces'
      title: Christian Graces
      number: 1
      content: Masters, give your bondservants what is just and fair, knowing that
        you also have a Master in heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Continue earnestly in prayer, being vigilant in it with thanksgiving; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'meanwhile praying also for us, that God would open to us a door for
        the word, to speak the mystery of Christ, for which I am also in chains, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: that I may make it manifest, as I ought to speak.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Walk in wisdom toward those who  are outside, redeeming the time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Final Greetings'
      title: Final Greetings
      number: 6
      content: Let your speech always be  with grace, seasoned with salt, that you
        may know how you ought to answer each one.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Tychicus, a beloved brother, faithful minister, and fellow servant
        in the Lord, will tell you all the news about me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am sending him to you for this very purpose, that he may know your
        circumstances and comfort your hearts, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: with Onesimus, a faithful and beloved brother, who is one of you.
        They will make known to you all things which are  happening here.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Aristarchus my fellow prisoner greets you, with Mark the cousin of
        Barnabas (about whom you received instructions: if he comes to you, welcome
        him), '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: and Jesus who is called Justus. These are  my only fellow workers
        for the kingdom of God who are of the circumcision; they have proved to be
        a comfort to me.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Epaphras, who is one of you, a bondservant of Christ, greets you,
        always laboring fervently for you in prayers, that you may stand perfect
        and complete in all the will of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For I bear him witness that he has a great zeal for you, and those
        who are in Laodicea, and those in Hierapolis. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Luke the beloved physician and Demas greet you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Closing Exhortations and Blessing'
      title: Closing Exhortations and Blessing
      number: 15
      content: Greet the brethren who are in Laodicea, and Nymphas and the church
        that is in his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now when this epistle is read among you, see that it is read also
        in the church of the Laodiceans, and that you likewise read the epistle from
        Laodicea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And say to Archippus, \u201CTake heed to the ministry which you have
        received in the Lord, that you may fulfill it.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "This salutation by my own hand\u2014Paul. Remember my chains. Grace
        be with you. Amen."
      comments: []
